<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hai X. Ma &amp; X. Y. Pan" authorityYear="2022" class="Ascomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Xylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xylaria polysporicola" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polysporicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylaria polysporicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. phyllocharis" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="phyllocharis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. phyllocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mont. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. phyllocharis" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="phyllocharis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. phyllocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has fully immersed perithecia, the fertile part with peg-like structures and smaller perithecia 0.2-0.3 mm diam (
<bibRefCitation author="San Martin, GF" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="283 - 373" refId="B38" refString="San Martin, GF, Rogers, JD, 1989. A preliminary account of Xylaria of Mexico. Mycotaxon 34: 283 - 373" title="A preliminary account of Xylaria of Mexico." volume="34" year="1989">
San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
and Rogers 1989
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1128/jb.172.8.4238-4246.1990" author="Fournier, J" journalOrPublisher="org" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="81 - 164" refId="B8" refString="Fournier, J, Lechat, C, Courtecuisse, R, 2020. The genus Xylaria sensu lato (Xylar-iaceae) in Guadeloupe and Martinique (French West Indies) III. Taxa with sl-ender upright stromata. Ascomycete. org 12 (3): 81 - 164, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1128/jb.172.8.4238-4246.1990" title="The genus Xylaria sensu lato (Xylar-iaceae) in Guadeloupe and Martinique (French West Indies) III. Taxa with sl-ender upright stromata. Ascomycete." url="https://doi.org/10.1128/jb.172.8.4238-4246.1990" volume="12" year="2020">Fournier et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hai X. Ma &amp; X. Y. Pan" authorityYear="2022" class="Ascomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Xylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xylaria polysporicola" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polysporicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylaria polysporicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Ascomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Xylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xylaria" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (80082005) from Taiwan in stromatal morphology, but the latter has slightly smaller stroma (11-14 mm total length 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm diam. vs. 10-40 mm total length 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.6 mm diam.), hard texture, slightly larger ascospores 13.5-16.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, with narrowly rounded ends (
<bibRefCitation author="Ju, YM" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="343 - 440" refId="B18" refString="Ju, YM, Rogers, JD, 1999. The Xylariaceae of Taiwan (excluding Anthostomella). Mycotaxon 73: 343 - 440" title="The Xylariaceae of Taiwan (excluding Anthostomella)." volume="73" year="1999">Ju and Rogers 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Ascomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Xylaria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xylaria phyllophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phyllophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylaria phyllophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ces. somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. polysporicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="polysporicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. polysporicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in stromatal morphology, but the former has larger ascospores 20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cooke, MC" journalOrPublisher="Grevillea" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="81 - 94" refId="B2" refString="Cooke, MC, 1883. On Xylaria and its allies. Grevillea 11: 81 - 94" title="On Xylaria and its allies." volume="11" year="1883">Cooke 1883</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
