<bibRefCitation author="San Martin, GF" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="283 - 373" refId="B38" refString="San Martin, GF, Rogers, JD, 1989. A preliminary account of Xylaria of Mexico. Mycotaxon 34: 283 - 373" title="A preliminary account of Xylaria of Mexico." volume="34" year="1989">
San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
and Rogers 1989
</bibRefCitation>
). In the phylogenetic tree, 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. polysporicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="polysporicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. polysporicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a lineage close to 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. amphithele" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="amphithele">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. amphithele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. ficicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="ficicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. ficicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distant from 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. phyllocharis" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="phyllocharis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. phyllocharis</emphasis>
